The paper deals with range spaces and geometric ranges, which are typical topics in computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). It also discusses the VC-dimension, which is a concept from statistical learning theory and information theory (cs.IT). The paper presents a new structure for estimating the quantity $|X \cap h|/|X|$ that is sensitive to the content of $X$, which involves measuring how much the ranges differ from each other in their intersections with $X$. This suggests a connection to clustering and data mining (cs.DM). Finally, the paper discusses the space complexity of the proposed structure, which is related to the theory of communication complexity (cs.CC).
